main event: A civilian woman observed disc-shaped objects flying in formation over Houlton, Maine, for 35 minutes on August 2, 1952.
interesting points: The objects flew in formation and some would leave and return to the formation., The sighting lasted for 35 minutes., No photographs were included in the report., The conclusion of the observation was insufficient data for evaluation., The report indicates that up to 21 individual light objects were observed.
